sequenceDiagram
    participant BO as Backoffice / Internal
    participant AC as api-catalogue
    participant MQ as RabbitMQ
    participant PP as Product Preparation
    participant CD as Catalogue Definition (lengow-core)
    participant FD as Feed Definition (lengow-core)
    participant FM as Feed Materialization (lengow-publishing)
    participant SNAP as MongoDB Feed Snapshot
    participant BAL as publishing-balancer
    participant PMP as pymarketplaces
    participant MK as Mirakl
    participant SRV as NetAmplify Serving Layer

    BO->>AC: Create or update product
    AC->>AC: Persist product
    AC->>MQ: Publish ProductMutationCommitted (via outbox)
    Note over AC: Legacy post_write HTTP call retired for API writes

    MQ->>PP: Deliver ProductMutationCommitted
    PP->>CD: Read catalogue definition (additional sources, fields, S&R, segments)
    PP->>PP: Apply shared derivation (joins, derived fields, segments)
    PP->>PP: Stamp snapshot with catalogue_definition_version_id
    PP->>MQ: Publish PreparedProductChanged

    MQ->>FM: Deliver PreparedProductChanged
    FM->>FD: Load feed definition (mappings, rules, exclusions, injections, category mapping)
    FM->>FM: Route per subscribed feed and per-feed eligibility
    FM->>FM: Apply feed-scoped materialization (per product, per feed)
    FM->>SNAP: Update feed snapshot (per product, incremental)
    FM->>MQ: Publish FeedProductPrepared

    MQ->>BAL: Deliver FeedProductPrepared (NetMarket feeds)
    BAL->>BAL: Apply quotas, feed locks, concurrency rules
    BAL->>PMP: Dispatch governed workload
    PMP->>SNAP: Read affected products from snapshot
    PMP->>MK: Push offers

    MQ->>SRV: Deliver FeedProductPrepared (NetAmplify feeds)
    Note over SRV: Invalidate cache or serve live from snapshot
    SRV->>SNAP: Stream products as CSV/XML/JSON on channel pull
